= <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> Congress

The <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has suffered severe internal conflicts the past year over Hugenberg's leadership, the Young Plan referendum with its controversial "imprisonment" paragraph, the resignation of Westarp in protest[? if young_plan_signatures >= 10:, the impending vote on it within the Reichstag ?], and the expulsion of their Reichstag member Gottfried Treviranus over a private letter suggesting a split within the party if Hugenberg is unable to be removed.

The "unity of the no" against Marxism has been losing its force over the years, and the referendum against the Young Plan has only exacerbated internal party tensions. Despite Hugenberg's efforts to increase control over the party, Westarp's resignation has set off a flurry of opposition within the party. [? if young_plan_signatures < 10: The failure of the initiative against the Young Plan has strengthened the dissidents position. ?][? if young_plan_signatures >= 10: The success of the initiative against the Young Plan to gather enough signatures has thrown a wrench in the dissident's plans. ?][? if was_in_right_coalition == 1: Many party members voice their dissatisfaction on Hugenberg's withdrawal from the government some time ago.?]

