The failure of the Young Plan referendum to reach the 10% threshold and the declining popularity of the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> has convinced the majority of the party to vote out Hugenberg, replacing him with Treviranus, a member of the "Young Conservative" wing of the party. The Young Conservatives are in favor of transforming the <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> into a "Tory democracy", advancing their goals in the framework of the system.

In response, Hugenberg threatens to take himself and his supporters into a new splinter party, which is unlikely to gain much support, considering he remains deeply unpopular beyond his loyal following.

